 related to the\nenrichment, and hence to the timescale of star-formation. Our results appear to\nbe consistent with the merger hypothesis for the formation of ellipticals which\npredicts that a significant fraction of the scatter is due to variations in the\nimportance of dissipation in forming merger remnants of a given mass.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 25 Feb 2009 14:39:42 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 23 Mar 2009 15:22:05 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-05-13"}
